A section of a building at Federal Polytechnic, Ede, Osun State was on Wednesday night razed by fire, causing apprehension on the campus, as the Public Relations Officer of the institution, Sola Lawal, said the cause of the fire was yet to be known. He disclosed that the building was a female hostel that was still under construction, adding that no live was lost except the affected property. He, however, commended the men of Osun State Fire Service and their Federal counterpart for prompt response to the distress call, which according to him, prevented escalation. When contacted, Administrative Officer of Osun State Fire Service, Fatai Aremu, said firemen in Oke Fia Unit received distress call from the scene late Wednesday and were immediately mobilized to the scene.